column5: Those look really long and skinny to be piranha.
Those look really long and skinny to be piranha. Well they are obviously malnourished, look at how aggressively they are feeding.
Well when I first saw the heading I thought "cold water" and then I saw the post. I'll take the cold water anytime!
Man I couldnt imagine accidentally falling out f the boat there..wow
Those dont look like pirahna to me either.  Whatever they are Im not swimming there?
Could be some sort of catfish.
Hard to tell the video was very grainy for me, that and hundreds of fish going nutso at one time lol
Nothing like my 2, 15 year olds.They will bite your hand,but look nothing like those.Mine are red belly's,cool video just the same,wonder what they are ?
Whatever they are I don't want to be in that water!!!
I wonder.... Baked or fried?  After seeing this it makes the video of the pike bite look like licking an ice cream cone...  G
Whatever they are, they probably wouldn't be too hard to catch! Pretty sure they'd eat a topwater, especially if you rolled it in ground beef first.
I think they may be Payara (vampire fish) which are a relative of the pirahna.  My son is studying marine biology at university, I've got him on the case and will see what he comes up with....
